                    <h3>Brooklyn Nine-Nine</h3>
                    <br>
                    <h4 id="bnn_synopsis">Synopsis</h4>
                    <p>Brooklyn Nine-Nine is a TV sitcom set in the 99th precinct of the <abbr title=New&nbsp;York&nbsp;&nbsp;City&nbsp;Police&nbsp;Department>NYPD</abbr> in Brooklyn. Main characters are the detectives working there and their captain. The series follows their adventures and conversations among them in a comedic way. Although it has elements from various genres such as romance and drama, the series focuses more on comedy and action.</p>
                    <br>
                    <h4 id="bnn_characters">Main characters</h4><br>
                    <table class="character-table">
                        <tr>
                            <td><img src="/img/bnn/bnn_jp.png" alt="Jake Peralta" width="240" height="240"></td>
                            <td><b>Jake Peralta</b><br><i>portrayed by Andy Samberg</i><br>A childish detective who is well-known for its success in the NYPD. Fan of Die Hard film series. Best friends with Boyle, close friends with Diaz, old friends with Linetti.</td>
                        </tr>
                          <tr>
                            <td><img src="/img/bnn/bnn_as.png" alt="Amy Santiago" width="240" height="240"></td>
                            <td><b>Amy Santiago</b><br><i>portrayed by Melissa Fumero</i><br>A detective who is too neat and worrywart about basically everything, especially if it’s work-related. Loves to be mentored by Captain Holt.</td>
                          </tr>
                          <tr>
                            <td><img src="/img/bnn/bnn_cb.png" alt="Charles Boyle" width="240" height="240"></td>
                            <td><b>Charles Boyle</b><br><i>portrayed by Jo Lo Truglio</i><br>A detective who loves cooking (anything food related actually). Obsessed with Jake Peralta. Has a huge family which he is very fond of.</td>
                          </tr>
                          <tr>
                            <td><img src="/img/bnn/bnn_rd.png" alt="Rosa Diaz" width="240" height="240"></td>
                            <td><b>Rosa Diaz</b><br><i>portrayed by Stephanie Beatriz</i><br>The toughest detective in the precinct. Not much is known about her as she doesn’t like talking about her life unrelated to the work. Close friends with Jake Peralta.</td>
                          </tr>
                          <tr>
                            <td><img src="/img/bnn/bnn_tj.png" alt="Terry Jeffords" width="240" height="240"></td>
                            <td><b>Terry Jeffords</b><br><i>portrayed by Terry Crews</i><br>Sergeant. Despite his tough look because of his muscular body and usually angry-looking face, he is very emotional and a total family man. Father of two daughters.</td>
                          </tr>
                          <tr>
                            <td><img src="/img/bnn/bnn_gl.png" alt="Gina Linetti" width="240" height="240"></td>
                            <td><b>Gina Linetti</b><br><i>portrayed by Chelsea Peretti</i><br>Captain Holt’s assistant, not a detective. Loves dancing and is very sassy. Even though she generally acts like an egomaniac, she likes to help her friends when they’re in a bad situation. Old friends with Jake Peralta.</td>
                          </tr>
                          <tr>
                            <td><img src="/img/bnn/bnn_rh.png" alt="Raymond Holt" width="240" height="240"></td>
                            <td><b>Raymond Holt</b><br><i>portrayed by Andre Braugher</i><br>Captain of 99. Very serious and organised. His feelings are impossible to tell by looking at his face. Often joked by Jake Peralta as he “talks like a robot” and “looks like a robot”.</td>
                          </tr>
                          <tr>
                            <td><img src="/img/bnn/bnn_mh.png" alt="Michael Hitchcock" width="240" height="240"></td>
                            <td><b>Michael Hitchcock</b><br><i>portrayed by Dirk Blocker</i><br>One of the oldest detectives in 99. Loves eating and sleeping on his chair. Best friends with Scully.</td>
                          </tr>
                          <tr>
                            <td><img src="/img/bnn/bnn_ns.png" alt="Norm Scully" width="240" height="240"></td>
                            <td><b>Norm Scully</b><br><i>portrayed by Joel McKinnon Miller</i><br>Another one of the oldest detectives. Also loves food and naps. Best friends with Hitchcock.</td>
                          </tr>
                    </table>
