                    <h3>The Office (U.S.)</h3>
                    <br>
                    <h4 id="toff_synopsis">Synopsis</h4>
                    <p>The Office (U.S.) is a TV sitcom set in the Scranton, PA branch of the fictional paper supply company Dunder Mifflin. The show was adapted from the UK series of the same name. It was filmed in a single camera setup as the footages are being recorded for a documentary which is filmed in the office. The show revolves around the employees of the office and the absurd incidents happening around them.</p>
                    <br>
                    <h4 id="toff_characters">Main characters</h4><br>
                    <table class="character-table">
                        <tr>
                            <td><img src="/img/toff/toff_ms.png" alt="Michael Scott" width="240" height="240"></td>
                            <td><b>Michael Scott</b><br><i>portrayed by Steve Carell</i><br>Manager of the Scranton branch. He's usually the trouble maker of the office with his silly ideas and his way of handling hardships happening in the office.</td>
                        </tr>
                          <tr>
                            <td><img src="/img/toff/toff_jh.png" alt="Jim Halpert" width="240" height="240"></td>
                            <td><b>Jim Halpert</b><br><i>portrayed by John Krasinski</i><br>A succesful salesmen in the office. One of the few sane people in the office, actually. Likes to kid around with Dwight Schrute. Likes to hang out with Beesly.</td>
                          </tr>
                          <tr>
                            <td><img src="/img/toff/toff_pb.png" alt="Pam Beesly" width="240" height="240"></td>
                            <td><b>Pam Beesly</b><br><i>portrayed by Jenna Fischer</i><br>Starts with being the receptionist of the office and promotes to saleswomanship soon. Likes to hang out with Halpert.</td>
                          </tr>
                          <tr>
                            <td><img src="/img/toff/toff_ds.png" alt="Dwight Schrute" width="240" height="240"></td>
                            <td><b>Dwight Schrute</b><br><i>portrayed by Rainn Wilson</i><br>Assistant <em>to the</em> Regional Manager of the branch. Or "Assistant Regional Manager" as he often puts it. A real hardworker and is very disciplined and organised. Often causes trouble to his colleagues in the effort of following his principles and consequently gets outsmarted by Halpert.
                            </td>
                          </tr>
                          <tr>
                            <td><img src="/img/toff/toff_rh.png" alt="Ryan Howard" width="240" height="240"></td>
                            <td><b>Ryan Howard</b><br><i>portrayed by B.J. Novak</i><br>Started as an intern and soon returned to the company as a salesman. Climbed up the corporate ladder and worked in the HQ in NY. Nevertheless fell quickly to the place he was before. A real entrepreneur.</td>
                          </tr>
                    </table>
